      <fieldvalue value="<div class=&quot;content_para&quot;><p>To offer best practice advice on the initial recognition, referral and diagnosis of children and young people with autism</p></div>"/>
    </field>
    <field fieldid="132" ordby="430" id="402" name="Target Population" type="text">
      <fieldvalue value="<div class=&quot;content_para&quot;><p>Children and young people on the autism spectrum from birth up to 19 years and their parents/carers</p></div>"/>
    </field>
    <field fieldid="133" ordby="435" id="403" name="Interventions and Practices Considered" type="text">
      <fieldvalue value="<ol style=&quot;list-style-type: decimal;&quot;>
    <li>Setting up a local autism multi-agency strategy group for recognition, referral, and diagnostic assessment of possible autism </li>
    <li>Recognizing signs and symptoms of autism in children and young people </li>
    <li>Discussing developmental or behavioural concerns about a child or young person with parents or carers </li>
    <li>Referring children and young people to the autism team </li>
    <li>Referral to a paediatrician or paediatric neurologist when appropriate </li>
    <li>Performing an autism diagnostic assessment and/or an alternative assessment </li>
    <li>Appointing a case coordinator for each child who is to have an autism diagnostic assessment </li>
    <li>Sharing and communicating information about the outcome of the autism diagnostic assessment with parents/caregivers and the child </li>
    <li>Performing a general physical examination </li>
    <li>Consideration of differential diagnosis including other neurodevelopmental and mental health disorders </li>
    <li>Diagnosis of autism based on International Classification of Disease, 10th Revision (ICD-10) or Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, Fourth Edition (DSM-IV) criteria </li>
    <li>Steps to take if there is uncertainty of an autism diagnosis (e.g., keeping child under continued review, referral for second opinion) </li>
    <li>Genetic testing or encephalography when appropriate </li>
    <li>Providing information and support to parents and families </li>
</ol>"/>
    </field>
    <field fieldid="134" ordby="440" id="404" name="Major Outcomes Considered" type="text">
      <fieldvalue value="<ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;>
    <li>Diagnostic accuracy (sensitivity, specificity) of clinical and other features for the recognition of autism spectrum disorders (ASD) </li>
    <li>Diagnostic accuracy of biomedical investigations in ASD </li>
    <li>Identification of coexisting conditions </li>
    <li>Health-related quality of life, measured in quality-adjusted life years (QALYs) </li>
</ul>"/>
    </field>
